    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="130" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d130">
                <head>No. 130.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-04-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 26,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 267.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 333, of the 13th instant,
                        inclosing a copy of a petition addressed to the minister of commerce by
                        French importers and dealers in American pork, has been read with interest
                        as a valuable indication of the tendency of sound opinion in France on the
                        question.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
